annotationA: Zinc transporter 63C, isoform F; Zinc transporter 63C (ZnT63C) is a plasma membrane resident zinc transporter belonging to the zinc transporter family that is mainly responsible for zinc export from the cell or into organelles. ZnT63C plays a key role in effluxing zinc from enterocytes into circulation during dietary zinc absorption
annotationB: Protein catecholamines up; Negatively regulates tyrosine hydroxylase activity
